==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effulge
<hw>Ef*fulge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Effulged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Effulging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>effulgere</ets> to shine forth; <ets>ex</ets> + <ets>fulgere</ets>
to flash, shine. See <er>Fulgent</er>.]</ety> <def>To cause to shine
with abundance of light; to radiate; to beam.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His eyes <qex>effulging</qex> a peculiar fire.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effulge</ent>⟦br⟧

